#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:6
msgid "Statistics"
msgstr "Statistiken"

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:9
msgid ""
"The OTRS statistics module holds features to track operational statistics "
"and generates custom reports associated with OTRS usage. The OTRS system "
"uses the term \"statistic\" generically to refer to a single report "
"presenting various indicators."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:13
msgid ""
"For <ulink url=\"https://www.otrs.com/solutions/\"><emphasis role=\"bold"
"\">OTRS Business Solution™</emphasis></ulink> customers, there is also a "
"reports generator available. Here \"report\" refers to a collection of "
"several statistics in one PDF document that can be easily configured and "
"automatically generated and distributed. Please find more details in the "
"<ulink url=\"http://otrs.github.io/doc/manual/otrs-business-solution/stable/"
"en/html/index.html\"><emphasis role=\"bold\">OTRS Business Solution™</"
"emphasis> manual</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:18
msgid ""
"Proper configuration of the OTRS statistics module is associated with a "
"multitude of requirements and considerations. These include the various OTRS "
"modules to be evaluated, user permission settings, indicators to be "
"calculated and their complexity levels, ease of configuration of the "
"statistics module, speed and efficiency of calculations, and support of a "
"rich set of output variants."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:22
msgid ""
"Statistical elements, i.e. files which supplement the functionality of the "
"statistics module for specific requirements, can be integrated for "
"calculating complex statistics."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:26
msgid "Statistics Configuration and Usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:29
msgid ""
"When signed on as an agent, the statistics module can be opened by selecting "
"\"Reports\" and then \"Statistics\" in the main menu."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:33
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Übersicht"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:36
msgid ""
"Selecting the \"Statistics\" link in the navigation bar, and then the "
"submenu link \"Overview\", calls up the Overview screen. The Overview screen "
"presents a list of all pre-configured reports the agent can use (see figure "
"below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:41
msgid "Overview of the standard statistics."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:43
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-overview.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-overview.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:49
msgid ""
"When the statistics module is installed, it comes preloaded with a few "
"sample statistics imported into the system. These are shown as a list on the "
"overview page. If the overview list extends to more than a single page, the "
"agent can browse through the different pages. The list of statistics can be "
"sorted as desired, by clicking the desired column header in the list. To "
"generate a particular statistic, click on the statistic's \"Run now\" link."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:54
msgid "Generation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:57
msgid ""
"The view user interface provides the stat's configuration settings (see "
"figure below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:62
msgid "Viewing a specific statistic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:64
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-view.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-view.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:70
msgid ""
"Configuration settings for a particular statistic can be set within the "
"range of options in the View screen. Either the statistic creator or any "
"others with the appropriate permissions can make the settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:74
msgid ""
"Pressing the \"Start\" button (at the bottom of the screen) is the last step "
"to generate the statistic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:82
msgid ""
"Agents with write rights can edit an existing report configuration by "
"calling up the edit user interface of the statistics module. Alternately, "
"they may create a new report."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:86
msgid ""
"There are four possible steps in the configuration of a statistic: the "
"general specification data, configuring the x-axis, y-axis and possible data "
"filters for the reported data (or restrictions).  Let's create a new "
"statistic as an example by clicking the \"Add\" button in the overview "
"screen.  Our goal will be to get an overview of how many tickets with very "
"high priority are in every queue (x-axis) and state (y-axis)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:94
msgid "Adding a new statistic, first step."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:96
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-add-typeselection."
"png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-add-typeselection."
"png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:102
msgid ""
"At the beginning we have to select the type of statistic we want to add. "
"Three types are available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:108
msgid "Dynamic Matrix Statistics"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:111
msgid ""
"This type of statistics will generate a matrix of computed values (e.g. new "
"tickets per day of month and queue).  All value cells in the matrix have the "
"same type (number, average time, etc.).  Values are computed from entities "
"in the system (e.g. tickets).  Some matrix statistics support a summation "
"column and/or row (only useful for certain data)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:119
msgid "Dynamic List Statistics"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:122
msgid ""
"This kind of statistic will generate a table where every line (not cell) "
"represents an entity in the system (e. g. a ticket).  The columns in this "
"row are usually configurable (x-axis, see below) and contain the data of "
"this object (e. g. ticket attributes).  All value cells in one column have "
"the same type."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:129
msgid "Static Statistics"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:132
msgid ""
"This kind of statistic is not very much configurable and usually used for "
"very special and/or complex computations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:106
msgid "<placeholder type=\"variablelist\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:140
msgid ""
"So let's select \"Dynamic Matrix\" for our example. Then the \"General "
"Specifications\" configuration will appear below the statistic type "
"selection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:144
msgid "Adding a new statistic, second step."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:146
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-add-general.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-add-general.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:151
msgid ""
"After providing a title and description for the new statistic, we have to "
"select the statistics backend that we want to use.  This is the actual "
"backend module which is responsible to collect and analyze the data for our "
"statistic.  In our case we'll select \"TicketAccumulation\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:156
msgid ""
"By configuring permission groups, we can facilitate a restriction of the "
"groups (and therefore, agents) who can later view and generate the pre-"
"configured statistics. Thus the various statistics can be allocated to the "
"different departments and work groups who need them. It is possible to "
"allocate one statistic to various groups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><example><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:160
msgid "Default statistics permission group"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><example><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:162
msgid ""
"The \"stats\" group was selected. The report is viewable for all users "
"having at least ro rights for the \"stats\" group. This access is available "
"by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><example><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:168
msgid "Customized statistics permission group"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><example><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:170
msgid ""
"A group named \"sales\" was selected. All users with ro rights for the "
"\"sales\" group can see the stat in the view mode and generate it. However, "
"the report will not be available for viewing by other users."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:175
msgid ""
"Additionally, possible output formats can be selected. Here we can just keep "
"all output formats and choose the one to use when actually generating the "
"statistic. Let's save the statistic now."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:179
msgid ""
"The next screen will indicate the next step with a highlighted button: we "
"should configure the x-axis. By clicking the button, a dialog will appear "
"where we can select the element to be used for the x-axis. In our case that "
"will be the queue:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:185
msgid "Configuring the x-axis of a statistic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:187
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-config-xaxis.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-config-xaxis.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:193
msgid ""
"We can optionally limit the queues to be shown by selecting some in the "
"queue field. With the checkbox we can control if the agent who generates the "
"statistic can make changes to the queue selection.  We'll keep the defaults "
"and press \"Save\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:198
msgid ""
"Now we can configure the y-axis in the same way: select the state field."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:203
msgid "Configuring the y-axis of a statistic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:205
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-config-yaxis.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-config-yaxis.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:211
msgid ""
"Here it is possible to select one element or two. In the first case, every "
"value of the element will be one element on the y-axis. If two elements are "
"selected, their permutations will be the elements on the value series.  For "
"example you could select \"state\" and \"priority\", and the resulting "
"elements will be \"new - 1 very low\", \"new - 2 low\", ... \"open - 1 very "
"low\" and so on. Let's just use the state and press \"Save\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:217
msgid ""
"Now in the last step we could add data filters to only report tickets "
"belonging to a certain customer, with certain priorities and so on. We'll "
"add a filter for very high priority tickets:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:223
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:240
msgid "Configuring the data filter of a statistic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:225
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-config-filter.png"
"\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"
msgstr ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/administration/stats/stats-config-filter.png"
"\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:231
msgid "Now press \"Save\" again. The configuration is finished."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/stats.xml:234
msgid ""
"You may already have noted that in the configuration dialog there is a "
"preview area where we can check the effect of our configuration settings."
