#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:244
msgid "Step 6: Configuring the Apache web server"
msgstr "Schritt 6: Konfiguration des Apache-Webservers"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:247
msgid ""
"First of all, you should install the Apache2 web server and mod_perl; you'd "
"typically do this from your systems package manager.  Below you'll find the "
"commands needed to set up Apache on the most popular Linux distributions."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:252
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# RHEL / CentOS:\n"
"shell> yum install httpd mod_perl\n"
"\n"
"# SuSE:\n"
"shell> zypper install apache2-mod_perl\n"
"\n"
"# Debian/Ubuntu:\n"
"shell> apt-get install apache2 libapache2-mod-perl2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:265
msgid ""
"Most <application>Apache</application> installations have a <filename>conf."
"d</filename> directory included.  On Linux systems you can usually find this "
"directory under <filename>/etc/apache</filename> or <filename>/etc/apache2</"
"filename>.  Log in as root, change to the <filename>conf.d</filename> "
"directory and link the appropriate template in <filename>/opt/otrs/scripts/"
"apache2-httpd.include.conf</filename> to a file called <filename>zzz_otrs."
"conf</filename> in the Apache configuration directory (to make sure it is "
"loaded after the other configurations)."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:273
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Debian/Ubuntu:\n"
"shell> ln -s /opt/otrs/scripts/apache2-httpd.include.conf /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/zzz_otrs.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:280
msgid ""
"OTRS requires a few Apache modules to be active for optimal operation. On "
"most platforms you can make sure they are active via the tool "
"<filename>a2enmod</filename>."
msgstr ""
"OTRS benötigt verschiedene aktivierte Apache Module, um optiomal zu laufen. "
"Auf den meisten Plattformen können Sie mit Hilfe des Tools "
"<filename>a2enmod</filename> prüfen, ob die Dienste aktiv sind."

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:285
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> a2enmod perl\n"
"shell> a2enmod version\n"
"shell> a2enmod deflate\n"
"shell> a2enmod filter\n"
"shell> a2enmod headers\n"
msgstr ""
"shell> a2enmod perl\n"
"shell> a2enmod version\n"
"shell> a2enmod deflate\n"
"shell> a2enmod filter\n"
"shell> a2enmod headers\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:295
msgid ""
"Now you can restart your web server to load the new configuration settings.  "
"On most systems you can do that with the command <command>systemctl restart "
"apache2.service</command>."
msgstr ""
"Starten Sie Ihren Webserver neu, um die neue Konfiguration zu laden. Auf den "
"meisten Systemen lässt sich der Webserver über den Befehl <command>systemctl "
"restart apache2</command> neu starten."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:301
msgid "Step 7: File Permissions"
msgstr "Schritt 7: Dateiberechtigungen"

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:308
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"shell> bin/otrs.SetPermissions.pl\n"
msgstr ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"shell> bin/otrs.SetPermissions.pl\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:316
msgid "Step 8: Database Setup and Basic System Configuration"
msgstr "Schritt 8: Datenbankeinrichtung und grundlegende Systemkonfiguration"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:318
msgid ""
"Please use the web installer at <ulink url=\"http://localhost/otrs/installer."
"pl\">http://localhost/otrs/installer.pl</ulink> (replace \"localhost\" with "
"your OTRS hostname) to setup your database and basic system settings such as "
"email accounts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:322
msgid ""
"The following configuration settings are recommended for MySQL setups. "
"Please add the following lines to <filename>/etc/my.cnf</filename> under the "
"[mysqld] section:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:339
msgid "Step 9: First login"
msgstr "Schritt 9: Erste Anmeldung"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:341
msgid ""
"Now you are ready to login to your system at <ulink url=\"http://localhost/"
"otrs/index.pl\">http://localhost/otrs/index.pl</ulink> with the credentials "
"you configured in the web installer (User: root@localhost)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:344
msgid "With this step, the basic system setup is finished."
msgstr "Nach diesem Schritt ist das Basis-Systemsetup beendet."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:349
msgid "Step 10: Start the OTRS Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:352
msgid ""
"The new OTRS daemon is responsible for handling any asynchronous and "
"recurring tasks in OTRS.  What has been in cron file definitions previously "
"is now handled by the OTRS daemon, which is now required to operate OTRS. "
"The daemon also handles all GenericAgent jobs and must be started from the "
"<literal>otrs</literal> user."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:359
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Daemon.pl start\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:366
msgid "Step 11: Cron jobs for the OTRS user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:368
msgid ""
"There are two default OTRS cron files in <filename>/opt/otrs/var/cron/*."
"dist</filename>, and their purpose is to make sure that the OTRS Daemon is "
"running.  They need to be be activated by copying them without the \".dist\" "
"filename extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:374
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/var/cron\n"
"shell> for foo in *.dist; do cp $foo `basename $foo .dist`; done\n"
msgstr ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/var/cron\n"
"shell> for foo in *.dist; do cp $foo `basename $foo .dist`; done\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:381
msgid ""
"To schedule these cron jobs on your system, you can use the script "
"<filename>Cron.sh</filename> with the <literal>otrs</literal> user."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:386
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh start\n"
msgstr "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh start\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:392
msgid "Stopping the cron jobs is also possible (useful for maintenance):"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:396
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh stop\n"
msgstr "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh stop\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:403
msgid "Step 12: Setup bash autocompletion (optional)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:405
msgid ""
"All regular OTRS commandline operations happen via the otrs Console "
"interface <filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl</filename>. This provides an auto "
"completion for the bash shell which makes finding the right command and "
"options much easier."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:410
msgid ""
"You can activate the bash autocompletion by installing the package "
"<literal>bash-completion</literal>.  It will automatically detect and load "
"the file <filename>/opt/otrs/.bash_completion</filename> for the "
"<literal>otrs</literal> user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:414
msgid ""
"After restarting your shell, you can just type <filename>bin/otrs.Console."
"pl</filename> followed by TAB, and it will list all available commands. If "
"you type a few characters of the command name, TAB will show all matching "
"commands. After typing a complete command, all possible options and "
"arguments will be shown by pressing TAB."
msgstr ""

